  "text": "While we were conducting this study, in December 2012, a new biofluids-specific RNA purification system became available (miRCURY RNA Isolation Kit -Biofluids from Exiqon). According to the manufacturer, this system provides improved yield and enhanced removal of PCR inhibitors. We have confirmed the outstanding performance of this system for small RNA isolation from both plasma and cerebrospinal fluid. [CITATION_1] With the goal of determining whether low RNA recovery or the presence of PCR inhibitors in our initial isolations could have contributed to largely negative results, we repeated the above experiments after isolating RNA with the Exiqon Biofluids procedure from previously unthawed macaque plasma. Despite greater recovery of endogenous miRNAs from plasma with this method, inconsistent amplification and high standard deviations . 1A ) in either of two macaque subjects designated \"67X\" and \"HL26.\" (B and C) Plasma miR160 and miR166 Cq values and standard deviations by time point and subject (67X and HL26). missing standard deviation bars are due to insufficient numbers of amplifying wells. Note that, to the extent it could be estimated, direction of apparent regulation often differed between the two subjects.",
